CAMELS is a standard risk measurement framework for banks that the FDIC uses when they evaluate banks for their soundness.

00:16:37.640 --> 00:16:44.640
The sprint for the FDIC tasks participants to think through how data can be used to alleviate operational risk.

00:16:45.640 --> 00:16:47.640
So what happens if somebody doesn't show up to work?

00:16:48.640 --> 00:16:49.640
