Maybe start thinking about how you can transfer that to a secure space that's maybe that's on a cloud environment so that others can access it besides you, because that type of data can be increasingly more important.

00:30:21.640 --> 00:30:25.640
So talking a little bit about this, it all starts with us, right?

00:30:26.640 --> 00:30:27.640
It all starts with everybody in the room.

00:30:27.640 --> 00:30:30.640
So how can you start with data analytics if you're not already doing this already?

00:30:31.640 --> 00:30:39.640
Make sure you're asking questions about data, ask for metrics, make your metrics specific, make it measurable so that people understand what you're looking for.

00:30:40.640 --> 00:30:45.640
And that can help drive the insights that you find and then the decisions that you make behind that.

00:30:46.640 --> 00:30:50.640
For inventory, you know, we ask what type of data do you have access to?

00:30:51.640 --> 00:30:53.640
I'm curious how many of your colleagues know what type of data you have, right?

00:30:53.640 --> 00:31:01.640
So finding the information that you have access to, maybe you'll discover that you have this whole other database you weren't even aware of.

00:31:02.640 --> 00:31:06.640
Maybe you find out that you're already collecting data about something you had questions about in the past.

00:31:07.640 --> 00:31:12.640
So especially in a lot of large organizations, we find that most people don't know what's available to them.

00:31:13.640 --> 00:31:14.640
And that's not just in terms of data.

00:31:15.640 --> 00:31:16.640
That's also in terms of tools.

00:31:17.640 --> 00:31:21.640
You know, maybe your organization already has our studio enterprise, right?

00:31:22.640 --> 00:31:23.640
And you weren't aware of that.

00:31:24.640 --> 00:31:27.640
So asking those types of questions can help you better understand that as well.

00:31:28.640 --> 00:31:32.640
And then, you know, for collaborating and talk to your colleagues.

00:31:33.640 --> 00:31:39.640
What we've seen is when you get a bunch of people in the room to start talking about the challenges that they're facing data or the data they have access to.

00:31:40.640 --> 00:31:43.640
You'll see that a lot of you are working on the same issues.

00:31:43.640 --> 00:31:51.640
And to be able to work together on that, you're, you know, instead of doubling the work because you're both solving it individually, solving it together tends to make that work go faster.

00:31:52.640 --> 00:32:00.640
And you might also see that there are other, you know, aspects and other data sources that you didn't realize you had.

00:32:03.640 --> 00:32:05.640
How can you support data literacy?

00:32:06.640 --> 00:32:11.640
So beyond actions that you're doing yourself, what can you do within an organization?

00:32:11.640 --> 00:32:14.640
Doing these types of lunch and learns internally, perhaps.

